annotationA: Seryl-tRNA synthetase, mitochondrial (SerRS-m) catalyses the aminoacylation of tRNAser with serine, to be used for gene translation during protein synthesis
annotationB: Probable glutamine--tRNA ligase; ATP binding; glutamine-tRNA ligase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: glutaminyl-tRNA aminoacylation; dendrite morphogenesis
